ZH:他整天闲着什么也不做。

EN: He sits idle all day and does nothing.

ZH: 她觉得很无聊，只能在家里闲着。

EN: She felt so bored that she could only stay idle at home.

ZH: 如果你闲下来，可以帮我买些东西吗？

EN: If you have some free time, could you help me buy some things?

ZH: 他常常在家里闲着，不做任何事情。

EN: He often idles at home, doing nothing.

ZH: 周末的时候，我喜欢闲着看电影。

EN: During weekends, I like to idle and watch movies.

ZH: 他可能会觉得很无聊，因为他总是闲着。

EN: He might feel bored because he is always idle.

ZH: 她不喜欢闲着，总是要找些事情做。

EN: She doesn't like to idle and always find something to do.

ZH: 如果你闲下来，我们可以一起去吃饭。

EN: If you have some free time, we can go eat together.

ZH: 天气很差，我们只能在屋里闲着。

EN: The weather is bad, so we can only idle indoors.

ZH: 下班以后他喜欢在公园闲着走走。

EN: After work, he likes to idle and walk in the park.

ZH: 忙完事情之后，他总是要闲一会。

EN: After finishing work, he always take a break and idle for a while.

ZH: 他就喜欢在家里闲着看电视。

EN: He just likes to idle at home and watch TV.

ZH: 对于他来说，闲闲地坐着也是享受。

EN: For him, idling and sitting leisurely is also enjoyable.

ZH: 我们的假期很长，我们可以闲着去旅游。

EN: Our holiday is long, we can idle and go travel.

ZH: 在周末的时候，我会闲着看书。

EN: During weekends, I will idle and read books.

ZH: 她一整天都在闲着，什么也没做。

EN: She idled all day, doing nothing.

ZH: 我们没有事情做，就在公园里闲着散步。

EN: We had nothing to do, so we idled in the park.

ZH: 虽然他闲着，但脑子里总是有很多事情。

EN: Although he is idling, his mind is always busy.

ZH: 在田野里闲着走走是一种享受。

EN: Idling and walking in the fields is a kind of enjoyment.
